The paper deals with the complexity of extending partial functions to coverage functions, which are a subclass of submodular functions. This involves concepts from machine learning, game theory, social networks, and facility location, which are all covered by various sub-categories of computer science. The paper also discusses the complexity of learning coverage functions, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
